---
description: API app (apps/api) NestJS rules — zod-first DTOs, plain guards, ownership predicate, client regen
globs: apps/api/**/*.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

- DTOs are zod-first via nestjs-zod (`createZodDto` + `@ZodResponse`); class-validator/class-transformer are lint-banned. detail: docs/guidelines/api-design.md
- Auth is plain guards + @nestjs/jwt — passport is lint-banned. detail: docs/guidelines/security.md
- Ownership is a query predicate: every tasks repo query filters `ownerId`; missing or foreign resources return 404, never 403.
- @nestjs/throttler TTLs are in MILLISECONDS, not seconds.
- Mongoose types never leave apps/api — wire contracts live in `@repo/schemas`, and `ownerId` is never on the wire.
- All errors flow through the global AllExceptionsFilter into the ErrorResponseSchema envelope — never hand-roll error shapes. detail: docs/guidelines/error-handling.md
- After any HTTP surface change run `pnpm gen:client` to regenerate `@repo/api-client` (generated output is committed and drift-checked).
